# Flask REST API Basics

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates the fundamentals of building a RESTful API using Flask in Python. The application performs basic CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations on a list of items using different HTTP methods. The API is tested using Postman, which allows sending requests and viewing JSON responses.

---

# Objectives

* Learn Flask web framework fundamentals.
* Understand REST API architecture.
* Implement CRUD operations using HTTP methods.
* Handle JSON requests and responses.
* Test API endpoints using Postman.
* Understand the role of Flask-CORS in API development.

---

# Technologies Used

## 1. Python

Python is the programming language used to build the application. It provides a simple syntax and extensive libraries for backend development.

Role:

* Develop backend logic.
* Process requests and responses.
* Handle data manipulation.

---

## 2. Flask

Flask is a lightweight Python web framework used to create web applications and REST APIs.

Role:

* Creates the web server.
* Defines API routes (endpoints).
* Handles HTTP requests and responses.
* Returns JSON data to clients.

Example:

```python
@app.route("/items", methods=["GET"])
```

---

## 3. Flask-CORS

Flask-CORS is an extension that enables Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS).

Role:

* Allows frontend applications running on different domains or ports to communicate with the Flask API.
* Prevents browser CORS restrictions during web application development.
* Makes the API accessible from external frontend applications.

Example:

```python
from flask_cors import CORS

CORS(app)
```

---

## 4. REST API

REST (Representational State Transfer) is an architectural style used for communication between clients and servers using HTTP methods.

HTTP Methods implemented in this project:

* GET – Retrieve data
* POST – Create new data
* PUT – Update existing data
* DELETE – Remove data

---

## 5. Postman

Postman is an API testing tool used to send HTTP requests and inspect server responses.

Role:

* Test all API endpoints.
* Send JSON request bodies.
* Verify status codes.
* Validate API functionality without creating a frontend application.

---

# API Documentation

## Base URL

http://127.0.0.1:5000

---

## 1. Home Endpoint

Method:

GET

Endpoint:

/

Description:

Returns a welcome message.

Response:

```
Hello, Flask!
```

---

## 2. Get All Items

Method:

GET

Endpoint:

/items

Description:

Returns all available items.

Example Response:

```json
[
    {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "Laptop"
    },
    {
        "id": 2,
        "name": "Mouse"
    },
    {
        "id": 3,
        "name": "Keyboard"
    }
]
```

---

## 3. Get Item by ID

Method:

GET

Endpoint:

/items/<id>

Example:

/items/2

Description:

Returns a specific item using its ID.

Example Response:

```json
{
    "id": 2,
    "name": "Mouse"
}
```

---

## 4. Add New Item

Method:

POST

Endpoint:

/items

Request Body:

```json
{
    "id": 4,
    "name": "Monitor"
}
```

Example Response:

```json
{
    "message": "Item added successfully",
    "item": {
        "id": 4,
        "name": "Monitor"
    }
}
```

---

## 5. Update Item

Method:

PUT

Endpoint:

/items/4

Request Body:

```json
{
    "name": "Gaming Monitor"
}
```

Example Response:

```json
{
    "message": "Item updated successfully",
    "item": {
        "id": 4,
        "name": "Gaming Monitor"
    }
}
```

---

## 6. Delete Item

Method:

DELETE

Endpoint:

/items/4

Description:

Deletes the specified item.

Example Response:

```json
{
    "message": "Item deleted successfully"
}
```

